---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Cibolo & Schertz, TX Real Estate | Cody Posey"
  description="Explore Cibolo and Schertz, Texas — family-friendly communities between San Antonio and New Braunfels. Top schools, safe neighborhoods, and convenient I-35 access."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="cs-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <span>Cibolo / Schertz</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Cibolo / <span style="color:#FF1616;">Schertz</span></h1>
        <p>Family-Friendly Communities Between SA & New Braunfels</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- City Intro -->
    <section class="section cs-intro">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cs-intro__grid">
          <div class="cs-intro__text">
            <h2>Two of the Most <span class="accent">Desirable Suburbs</span></h2>
            <p>Cibolo and Schertz are two of the most desirable suburban communities in the I-35 corridor. With A-rated SCUCISD schools, safe neighborhoods, and proximity to Randolph AFB, these cities offer a strong sense of community with big-city access. Over the past two decades, both cities have experienced rapid but well-managed growth, transforming from small towns into thriving suburban hubs that consistently rank among the best places to live in Texas.</p>
            <p>Located just 20 minutes from San Antonio and 15 minutes from New Braunfels, the Cibolo/Schertz area has grown into a combined population of over 75,000 — and continues to attract families, military personnel, and professionals looking for quality schools, affordable housing, and a convenient location along the I-35 corridor. The area sits at the intersection of I-35 and FM 3009, making it easy to reach downtown San Antonio, the San Antonio International Airport, and the booming commercial corridor along I-35 between San Antonio and Austin.</p>
            <p>What makes Cibolo and Schertz stand out from other San Antonio suburbs is the combination of top-rated schools, family-oriented neighborhoods, and a genuine community feel. Both cities have invested heavily in parks, trails, community centers, and public events. The Schertz Civic Center regularly hosts concerts, festivals, and farmers markets, while Cibolo has developed an impressive network of walking and biking trails that connect neighborhoods to parks and retail areas.</p>
            <p>The housing market here offers strong value for buyers. You will find a mix of established neighborhoods built in the early 2000s with mature landscaping and larger lots, alongside newer master-planned communities with modern floor plans and community amenities like pools, playgrounds, and splash pads. Price points typically range from the low $200s for older homes to the mid-$400s for newer construction with upgraded finishes. Compared to neighborhoods on the north side of San Antonio with similar school ratings, Cibolo and Schertz often deliver more square footage per dollar.</p>
            <p>The military community is a defining feature of the area. Randolph Air Force Base, now part of Joint Base San Antonio, is located just minutes away, and a significant percentage of residents are active-duty service members, veterans, or civilian employees of the Department of Defense. This creates a welcoming, diverse, and transient-friendly community where newcomers are easily integrated. As a veteran myself, I understand the unique needs of military families navigating PCS moves and VA loan purchases, and I work with a lot of buyers in that situation.</p>
            <p>Retail and dining options have expanded significantly in both cities. The Schertz Parkway corridor and FM 3009 are lined with restaurants, shopping centers, and entertainment venues. H-E-B, Target, Home Depot, and dozens of local and chain restaurants are all within a short drive. For bigger outings, The Forum shopping center in Selma is right next door, and downtown San Antonio and the Pearl District are about 20 minutes away.</p>
            <p>For families with children, the school district is often the deciding factor. SCUCISD has earned consistent A ratings from the Texas Education Agency, with strong academic programs, competitive athletics, and a wide range of extracurricular activities. The district's high schools — including Steele and Samuel Clemens — are well-regarded, and newer elementary and middle school campuses have been built to keep pace with the area's growth.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-intro__stats">
            <div class="cs-stat">
              <span class="cs-stat__number">75,000+</span>
              <span class="cs-stat__label">Population</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat">
              <span class="cs-stat__number">20 min</span>
              <span class="cs-stat__label">To San Antonio</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat">
              <span class="cs-stat__number">15 min</span>
              <span class="cs-stat__label">To New Braunfels</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat">
              <span class="cs-stat__number">A-Rated</span>
              <span class="cs-stat__label">Schools</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why People Move Here -->
    <section class="section cs-why" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Why People <span class="accent">Choose Cibolo / Schertz</span></h2>
          <p>The most common reasons buyers choose this area</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-why__grid">
          <div class="cs-why__card">
            <h3>Top Schools</h3>
            <p>A-rated Schertz-Cibolo-Universal City ISD (SCUCISD) serves the area, anchored by Steele High School. Families consistently rank schools as a top reason for moving here.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-why__card">
            <h3>Military-Friendly</h3>
            <p>Just 20 minutes from Randolph AFB, the area has a diverse and welcoming military community. Many active-duty and veteran families call Cibolo and Schertz home.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-why__card">
            <h3>Safe Communities</h3>
            <p>Family-oriented neighborhoods with low crime rates, well-maintained parks, and a strong sense of community make this area ideal for raising a family.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-why__card">
            <h3>Convenient Location</h3>
            <p>Positioned along the I-35 corridor between San Antonio and New Braunfels, with growing retail, dining, and services. Easy access to both metros for work and entertainment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation Cards -->
    <section class="section cs-explore">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Explore <span class="accent">Cibolo / Schertz</span></h2>
          <p>Dig deeper into the neighborhoods, homes, and lifestyle that matter to you</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-explore__grid">
          <a href="/cibolo-schertz/neighborhoods/" class="cs-explore__card">
            <h3>Neighborhoods</h3>
            <p>Explore the top communities in Cibolo and Schertz — from established favorites to newer developments.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="https://cposeyrealestate.idxbroker.com/idx/search/advanced" class="cs-explore__card">
            <h3>Home Search</h3>
            <p>Search current listings in Cibolo and Schertz. Filter by price, area, and home type to find what's available now.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/cibolo-schertz/restaurants/" class="cs-explore__card">
            <h3>Restaurants</h3>
            <p>From wings and Tex-Mex to authentic Thai — the best local spots to eat in the Cibolo/Schertz area.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/cibolo-schertz/things-to-do/" class="cs-explore__card">
            <h3>Things to Do</h3>
            <p>Nature parks, wildlife safaris, live entertainment, and outdoor adventures in and around the area.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- School District -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>School <span class="accent">District</span></h2>
          <p>One of the highest-rated school districts in the San Antonio metro</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-schools__grid">
          <a href="https://www.scuc.txed.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-schools__card">
            <h3>Schertz-Cibolo-Universal City ISD (SCUCISD)</h3>
            <p>An A-rated district known for academic excellence, strong athletics, and community engagement. Steele High School and Byron P. Steele II are among the top-rated campuses. The district serves Schertz, Cibolo, and Universal City.</p>
            <span class="cs-schools__link">Visit SCUCISD Website →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section cs-cta" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to Explore <span class="accent">Cibolo / Schertz</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">Whether you're just starting your search or ready to schedule showings, I can help you navigate the market and find the right fit.</p>
        <div class="cs-cta__buttons">
          <a href="https://cposeyrealestate.idxbroker.com/idx/search/advanced" class="btn btn-primary">Search Homes</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Ask About Cibolo / Schertz</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About <span class="accent">Cibolo and Schertz</span></h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What are home prices like in Cibolo and Schertz?</summary>
            <p>Home prices in the Cibolo and Schertz area typically range from the low $200s for older resale homes to the mid-$400s for newer construction in master-planned communities. The median home price generally falls in the mid-$300s, which represents strong value compared to neighborhoods in north San Antonio with comparable school ratings. New construction communities like Deer Creek Ranch, Cibolo Canyons, and Verde Ranch offer modern floor plans with community amenities at competitive price points. If you are looking for a specific price range, I can set up a custom search to show you exactly what is available right now.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How are the schools in Cibolo and Schertz?</summary>
            <p>The area is served by Schertz-Cibolo-Universal City ISD (SCUCISD), which consistently earns A ratings from the Texas Education Agency. The district is known for strong academics, competitive athletics, and a wide range of extracurricular programs. High schools in the district include Byron P. Steele II and Samuel Clemens, both of which have strong reputations. The district has also built several new elementary and middle school campuses in recent years to accommodate growth. Schools are one of the top reasons families choose this area, and the district's performance is a major factor in the strong resale values here.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is Cibolo/Schertz a good area for military families?</summary>
            <p>Absolutely. The Cibolo and Schertz area is one of the most military-friendly communities in the San Antonio metro. Randolph Air Force Base, part of Joint Base San Antonio, is just minutes away, and a large percentage of residents are active-duty, retired military, or DoD civilians. The community is welcoming to newcomers, which is important for families who move frequently. VA loans are widely used and accepted here, and many of the newer neighborhoods were specifically designed to appeal to military families with features like community pools, parks, and proximity to base. As a veteran, I have firsthand experience helping military families navigate PCS moves and find the right home in this area.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png" />

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to learn more about Cibolo / Schertz..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are home prices like in Cibolo and Schertz?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Home prices in the Cibolo and Schertz area typically range from the low $200s for older resale homes to the mid-$400s for newer construction in master-planned communities. The median home price generally falls in the mid-$300s, which represents strong value compared to neighborhoods in north San Antonio with comparable school ratings."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How are the schools in Cibolo and Schertz?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The area is served by Schertz-Cibolo-Universal City ISD (SCUCISD), which consistently earns A ratings from the Texas Education Agency. The district is known for strong academics, competitive athletics, and a wide range of extracurricular programs. High schools in the district include Byron P. Steele II and Samuel Clemens."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Cibolo/Schertz a good area for military families?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Absolutely. The Cibolo and Schertz area is one of the most military-friendly communities in the San Antonio metro. Randolph Air Force Base, part of Joint Base San Antonio, is just minutes away, and a large percentage of residents are active-duty, retired military, or DoD civilians."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: #f9f9f9;
  }
  .faq-section h2 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .faq-list {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .faq-item {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #eee;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .faq-item summary {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 1rem;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: #FF1616;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after {
    content: '\2212';
  }
  .faq-item p {
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .cs-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 320px;
    background: url('/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .cs-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .cs-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 1rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Breadcrumb */
  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  /* Intro */
  .cs-intro__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .cs-intro__text p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cs-intro__stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-stat {
    background: var(--light-gray);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .cs-stat__number {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .cs-stat__label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Why Section */
  .cs-why__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .cs-why__card {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .cs-why__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cs-why__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Explore Cards */
  .cs-explore__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-explore__card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--light-gray);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .cs-explore__card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .cs-explore__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #000;
  }

  .cs-explore__card:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .cs-explore__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Schools */
  .cs-schools__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cs-schools__card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cs-schools__card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .cs-schools__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #000;
  }

  .cs-schools__card:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .cs-schools__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cs-schools__link {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cs-cta__buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cs-intro__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cs-why__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cs-explore__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
